#: ../../../customisation/landing-page.md:1
msgid "Changing landing page"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/landing-page.md:3
msgid ""
"It is possible to have a custom landing page in Sphinx documentation. This "
"is achieved by adding a custom template file for that page and setting "
"[`html_additional_pages`][additional-pages] in `conf.py`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/landing-page.md:5
msgid ""
"templates_path = [\"_templates\"]\n"
"html_additional_pages = {\"index\": \"your-custom-landing-page.html\"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/landing-page.md:11
msgid ""
"You'll need to write HTML for the page in `_templates/your-custom-landing-"
"page.html`, if you use the above example as-is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/landing-page.md:14
msgid ""
"In case you're curious, this works because Sphinx allows overwriting "
"existing files when generating the website and processes "
"`html_additional_pages` _after_ processing the pages normally. These two "
"behaviours combined mean that we can overwrite the page generated with the "
"default layout by specifying the same document with a different template in "
"`html_additional_pages`."
msgstr ""
